Though Mr . McGregor said that donations from foreign companies was well - meant to help victims , he also pointed out that , “ if you ’ re a foreign company in China these days , you ’ re an open target for both attacks form people on the Internet and also government entities and the government media , so I think the default is always to anticipate that you ’ ll have trouble and try to get ahead of it .” Responding to the news of Apple ’ s donations , microblog users were mostly positive , with some taking the chance to hit out at China ’ s state - owned enterprises .